'''Mount Tengu''' (天狗山, Tengu-yama) is a mountain located in {{ill|Kofu|ja|甲府市}}, {{ill|Yamanashi Prefecture|ja|山梨県}}, Japan. It is situated at the southern edge of the {{ill|Okuchichibu Mountains|ja|奥秩父山塊}} and has an elevation of 493 meters. It is recognized as one of the {{ill|Famous Mountains of Kofu|ja|甲府名山}}.

== Overview ==
Mount Tengu is located in Haguro Town, Kofu City, and offers panoramic views of the {{ill|Kofu Basin|ja|甲府盆地}} from its summit. The mountain serves as the sacred body of the nearby Haguro Ōmiya Shrine. A trail from the shrine leads to the summit and continues toward {{ill|Chiyoda Lake|ja|千代田湖}}.

At the summit lies the O-Tengu-san Burial Mound (Mount Tengu Burial Mound), a {{ill|circular burial mound|ja|円墳}} with a stone mound approximately 30 meters in diameter and 6 meters in height. It is the largest stone mound burial site in Yamanashi Prefecture.<ref>[https://www.city.kofu.yamanashi.jp/koho/kaifukoramu/timei06.html Kofu City Official Site - Column on the Origin of Place Names]</ref> The area is dotted with shrines, altars, stone monuments, and pillars.

== Neighboring Mountains ==
* {{ill|Katayama (Yamanashi Prefecture)|ja|片山 (山梨県)}}

== Related Topics ==
* {{ill|Okuchichibu Mountains|ja|奥秩父山塊}}
