'''Mount Tengu''' (天狗山, Tengu-yama) is a mountain located in [[:en:Kōfu|Kofu]], [[:en:Yamanashi Prefecture|Yamanashi Prefecture]], Japan. It is situated at the southern edge of the [[:en:Okuchichibu Mountains|Okuchichibu Mountains]] and has an elevation of 493 meters. It is recognized as one of the {{ill|Famous Mountains of Kofu|ja|甲府名山|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Famous Mountains of Kofu|qq=|1=Kofu Meizan|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q109365123}}.

== Overview ==
Mount Tengu is located in Haguro Town, Kofu City, and offers panoramic views of the {{ill|Kōfu Basin|lt=Kōfu Basin|lt=Kofu Basin|ja|甲府盆地|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kofu Basin|qq=}} from its summit. The mountain serves as the sacred body of the nearby Haguro Ōmiya Shrine. A trail from the shrine leads to the summit and continues toward {{ill|Chiyoda Lake|ja|千代田湖|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chiyoda Lake|qq=|1=Lake Chiyoda|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11405318}}.

At the summit lies the O-Tengu-san Kofun (Mount Tengu Kofun), a {{ill|circular Kofun|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/circular Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Round Kofun|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} with a stone mound approximately 30 meters in diameter and 6 meters in height. It is the largest stone mound burial site in Yamanashi Prefecture.<ref>[https://www.city.kofu.yamanashi.jp/koho/kaifukoramu/timei06.html Kofu City Official Site - Column on the Origin of Place Names]</ref> The area is dotted with shrines, altars, stone monuments, and pillars.

